This paper deals with a communication system and its optimization for energy efficiency, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The use of multiple antennas and the analysis of the impact of cell size suggest that it could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Architecture (cs.AR) categories. Finally, the consideration of power consumption and efficiency makes the System and Control (cs.SY) category a possibility as well.
